{
  "stem": "10835.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we would just, on a nice day, we would go out in the yard and-- and relax.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And do like-- like any worker, except that we were-- we were imprisoned because we didn't have any freedom to go anywhere.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, at first, we-- as I said, at first we were able to mail cards, letters, and we were able to receive it back.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We didn't know where our brother was until, when my brother was able to communicate with our parents, that's when they notified us where he was at.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But we were not able to communicate with him, because, since we were able to communicate with the outside world, we were not able to communicate with another camp.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that was-- and that's the way it was going on for, I would say, two years.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was always fear.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was always fear.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We also had, since we worked with the Czech and German people in the factory, some of them were very kind.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they would give us a little food, which we really appreciated, of course.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And still we lived.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We lived.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You know, the-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the woman who was running the camp, she was called Lagerfuhrerin.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "She was the camp-- the kommand-- the kommandant, the woman camp kommandant.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Her husband was like a liaison between the factory and the camp.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he was a real spy.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He was spying on the girls.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "If they got-- get too chummy with the population, the Czech and the German population, and if he saw something that he didn't like, he reported it to his wife.",
      "word_count": 30
    }
  ],
